confident /ˈkɒnfɪdənt/

1. ADJ If you are confident about something, you are certain that it will happen in the way you want it to. 有信心的 

例： I am confident that everything will come out right in time. 我相信最终一切都会好起来的。 

例： Mr. Ryan is confident of success. 瑞安先生对成功有信心。 

2. confidently ADV 有信心地 [ADV with v] 

例： I can confidently promise that this year is going to be very different. 我可以有信心地保证今年将大不一样。 

3. ADJ If a person or their manner is confident , they feel sure about their own abilities, qualities, or ideas. 自信的 

例： In time he became more confident and relaxed. 最终他变得更加自信而从容了。 

4. confidently ADV 自信地 

例： She walked confidently across the hall. 她自信地走过大厅。 

5. ADJ If you are confident that something is true, you are sure that it is true. A confident statement is one that the speaker is sure is true. 确信的 

例： She is confident that everybody is on her side. 她确信每个人都在她那一边。 

6. confidently ADV 确信地 [ADV with v] 

例： I can confidently say that none of them were or are racist. 我可以确信地说他们当中没有人过去或现在是种族主义者。

